<subSubSection id="C3606530B3178A01FCFBFA9CFB75FA27" pageId="4" pageNumber="69" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC536BBB3178A01FCFBFA9CFB75FA27" blockId="4.[805,1406,1287,1981]" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis id="B90EEAA9B3178A01FCFBFA9CFC41FAA1" box="[833,984,1287,1313]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="69">Distribution.</emphasis>
Widespread in the West Indies in coastal forests, forest margins and on beach margins, often on coral or calcareous soils, from 0-100 m. Absent from Hispaniola, but found on Ile la Tortue and Ile la Navasse off the NW coast of Haiti.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
